ANTHRAX - INDONESIA: (EAST JAVA) LIVESTOCK, HUMANS, SUSPECTED
*************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Sun 6 Jun 2021
From: Mahmoud Orabi <ahstandards@gmail.com> [edited]


Media news articles (1,2,3) on [5 Jun 2021], reported that at least 6 residents of Sidomulo Village, Pejarvjo District, Tulunggung Regency experienced skin signs similar to those of anthrax with blisters on the skin forming itching circles. "Anthrax in Pajervojo (sub-district), information has spread to humans. There are 6 residents who are (already) contaminated, their skin is punctured," said an unnamed source with an ASN background on [Sat 5 Jun 2021]

When this information was confirmed to officials at the Tulunggung District Health Office, Didik Eka, the head of disease prevention and control, did not immediately confirm claiming that the issue was the domain of the leadership. He felt that he was not entitled to make a statement despite having preliminary data and information about anthrax outbreaks in livestock, which local residents suspected of having contracted the disease.

"Honestly, I don't dare to comment. This area is still in the lead. So if that's the case, please go straight to the (Head of Health) Office of Health Services," Didik said. However, upon learning that an issue of anthrax in cattle in Pejarvjo had been published in the mass media quoting a direct statement from the regent of Tulunggung Marito Birovo, Didik later confirmed the information that 6 residents had a skin disease with changes very similar to those of anthrax.

Links to the news:
1. https://henryclubs.com/six-residents-experienced-symptoms-of-skin-blisters-suspected-of-anthrax/
2. https://www.world-today-news.com/6-tulungagung-residents-suffer-from-skin-blisters-and-itching-suspected-of-having-anthrax-okezone-news/
3. https://www.notiulti.com/6-residentes-de-tulungagung-sufren-de-ampollas-en-la-piel-y-picazon-se-sospecha-que-tienen-antrax-okezone-news/

